# Dead-Mans - project rules for AI agents

## Active contour

- Active code lives only in `frontend/` and `backend/`.
- `legacy-v1/` is reference-only. Use it to study old logic or UX, but do not add new code there and do not copy code from it directly.

## Repo architecture

### Frontend

- `frontend/src/app/` - providers, bootstrap, theme, router wiring.
- `frontend/src/routes/` - route config and role-aware navigation helpers.
- `frontend/src/layouts/` - app shells and shared page layouts.
- `frontend/src/features/` - feature-first modules. Keep UI, hooks, and feature-facing data access inside the feature.
- `frontend/src/shared/api/client/` - HTTP transport only.
- `frontend/src/shared/api/config.ts` - env-driven API configuration.
- `frontend/src/shared/api/contracts/` - generated transport types and stable aliases.
- `frontend/src/shared/api/mocks/` - mock implementations.
- `frontend/src/shared/auth/` - auth and route guards.
- `frontend/src/shared/session/` - UI persistence helpers only.
- `frontend/src/locales/` - language resources. `frontend/src/i18n.ts` should only wire them together.

### Backend

- `backend/Api/Contracts/` - HTTP DTO only.
- `backend/Application/` - use-case services, application models, repository ports.
- `backend/Domain/` - domain entities and business rules.
- `backend/Infrastructure/` - adapters and DI. In-memory code belongs here as temporary storage adapters.
- `backend/Controllers/` - thin HTTP layer.
- `backend/openapi/deadmans.v1.yaml` - canonical transport source of truth.

## Contract rules

- Do not hand-maintain transport contracts in multiple places.
- Backend OpenAPI file `backend/openapi/deadmans.v1.yaml` is the transport source of truth.
- Frontend types should be generated from OpenAPI and re-exported through `frontend/src/shared/api/contracts/index.ts`.

## Frontend rules

- Keep business logic out of page components. Put it in hooks or feature model modules.
- Page components must consume feature-facing data access, not raw mocks.
- Use hierarchical query keys from `frontend/src/shared/api/queryKeys.ts`.
- Prefer switching between mock and HTTP through env/config, not by rewriting feature code.
- All user-facing text goes through i18n.
- Shared should not become a dump for feature-specific domain logic.

## Backend rules

- Controllers should depend on application services, not on infrastructure adapters.
- Infrastructure must implement repository ports; it must not own application orchestration.
- Keep transport DTO separate from application contracts and domain models.
- Business rules belong in Domain or Application, not in infrastructure adapters.

## Development workflow

- Update `README.md`, `STACK.md`, `CONTEXT.md`, and architecture docs when making structural changes.
- Keep mock mode usable, but treat HTTP mode as the target path.
- Before adding a new feature, decide where its use case lives in both frontend and backend.
